RAIL SPLITTER WIND FARM LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Rail Splitter Wind Farm LLC ("Rail Splitter") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Rail Splitter generating facility ("Rail Splitter Facility").
The Rail Splitter Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Tazewell County, Illinois. The Rail Splitter Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Rail Splitter's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Rail Splitter Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Rail Splitter's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Rail Splitter shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $554,860.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $46,238.33.
